FBIS3-9381 "dreeu057_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Mar 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Croat-Muslim Truce Violated in Mostar LD2303164794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1600 GMT 23 Mar 94 LD2303164794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] After more than a month of almost complete calm, a state of general alert was sounded in Mostar at 1544 today. According to the information and monitoring center of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna, Muslim snipers from east Mostar have shot one person dead and wounded another in the part of town controlled by the Croatian Defense Council [HVO]. The truce between the HVO and the Muslim army is being honored along all the other separation lines. [passage omitted]
